                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 855.48/35</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1302fn1">Forwarded to the Ambassador in France November 10,
                        No. 253.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-09">
                        <hi rend="italic">November 9, 1914</hi>.</date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 3 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>1027. The French Minister in Holland caused embarrassing situation regard
                    forwarding of food to Belgium saying he lacked instructions from his Government;
                    more cargoes will arrive forthwith.</p>
                <p>Can French Government not send him instructions soon as possible to consent to
                    transshipment through Holland as all other Governments consent?</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
